thread.title: Irish monthly retail sales growth rebounds to five-month high

title: Irish monthly retail sales growth rebounds to five-month high
text:
May 28, 2018 / 10:53 AM / Updated 14 minutes ago Irish monthly retail sales growth rebounds to five-month high Reuters Staff 1 Min Read
DUBLIN (Reuters) - Irish retail sales growth rebounded to a five-month high of 1.5 percent in April after falling almost 2 percent the previous month, data showed on Monday.
The annual growth rate was 4.8 percent in April, or 3.8 percent when volatile car sales are excluded, the Central Statistics Office said. Reporting by Conor Humphries; Editing by David Goodman
